\n<Therapist><WordWrap> Hey bud!\| Listen, I’ve got some general tips for you to think about as you complete the homework I gave you earlier.
\n<Therapist><WordWrap>The mind is a tricky thing.\| Sometimes it tries to help us by hiding away certain facts that hurt us.\|
It does this to prevent us from being emotionally overwhelmed as we work through the shock to process the event in front of us.
\n<Therapist><WordWrap>You can think of the mind as being partially made up of \c[4]movable blocks, locked doors\c[0] and \c[4]switches\c[0].
\n<Therapist><WordWrap>The \c[4]blocks\c[0] clutter your mind and prevent you from moving forward.\| Negative thoughts that get in
the way of progress.\| Often,\. these can be moved out of the way or made beneficial by moving
them in the right spot to activate a \c[4]switch.\c[0]

\n<Therapist><WordWrap>\c[4]Switches\c[0] are small epiphanies that we already knew,\. it just takes some thinking,\. or rearranging of thoughts to find and activate them.\| They can open \c[4]doors\c[0] that have previously blocked our path.

\n<Therapist><WordWrap>\c[4]Locked Doors\c[0] are more rigid barriers.\| Intentional roadblocks that our minds have set up to prevent us from proceeding,\. from dealing with trauma.\| These can be unlocked through \c[4]switches\c[0] that help us realize that what’s behind the door may be hard to deal with and hurt but it could also be what we need to move forward and unlock more \c[4]doors\c[0].
\n<Therapist><WordWrap>Anyway,\. some food for thought.\| I hope some of what I said can help you,\. I’ll call back every so often to check in.
\n<Therapist><WordWrap>Remember,\. if you get stuck mentally or just need to rest, you can always go to \c[4]Bed\c[0] and \c[4]Reset\c[0] for the day. Try again tomorrow
